Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_module_model_context(25.10)            write_module_model_context(25.10)

Name
       write_module_model_context  -  Creates  a  context model for a specific
       cell or a master/clone instance

Syntax
       write_module_model_context

       [-help]

       {-cell <cellName> | -master_clone_inst <master_clone_inst>}

       [-tag t<ag_name>]

       [-type {extraction_context timing_context}]

       [-type_specific_options <type_specific_options>]

       Creates a context model for a specific cell or a master/clone instance.
       This context model can be loaded additionally with its design later  in
       the flow.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies  the cell name(s) to be loaded. You can specify a list
              of cell names.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each write_module_model_context parameter. For a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command:

              man write_module_model_context

       -master_clone_inst <instance_name>
              Specifies the instance name of a master/clone module.  Use  this
              option if the instance has clone(s).

              Data_type: string, optional

       -tag <tag_name>
              Specifies the output tag name.

              Default: latest

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type {extraction_context timing_context}
              Specifies the type of the generated context model.

              * extraction_context:  Writes the extraction context information
                of specified modules/instances.

              * timing_context: Writes the timing context information of spec-
                ified modules/instances.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -type_specific_options
              Specifies the options of the type model.

              * For  extraction_context  type  of model, the type specific op-
                tions available are:

                {-extension <distance> |  -surrounding_tag  <name>  |  -ground
                <name>}

                * -extension <distance>

                  Specifies the block halo distance (in microns) where routing
                  data will be included in an output DEF file.

                  Default: 10

                * -surrounding_tag name

                  Specifies the surrounding object tag name.

                  Default: Tag name of the current loaded design.

                * -ground name

                  Specifies  the  ground net that the surrounding nets will be
                  tied to.

              * For timing_context type of model, the  type  specific  options
                available are:

                {-skip_interface_paths | -overwrite | -with_constraints}

                * -skip_interface_paths

                  Specify this option if the module is instantiated many times
                  at  the  full-chip top design. It preserves the context data
                  impacting only internal reg-reg paths. During analysis  with
                  this context data, interface paths will be unconstrained.

                * -overwrite

                  Specify this option to overwrite the existing timing_context
                  model. It overwrites the existing context data.

                *

                  -with_constraints

                  Specify  this  option  to  write the SDC file of each of the
                  specified module inside the corresponding  sub  directories.
                  This  option  is  supported only in SMSC flow and for single
                  instantiated modules.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command creates an extraction context model  for
                cell  ptn_wrapper with routing data within 50 micron halo dis-
                tance from ptn_wrapper LEF boundary:

                restore_module_model dtmf_recvr_core -tag init -noTiming

                # Ensure that routing to be cut around specified object should
                be a LEF

                set_module_model  -cell  ptn_wrapper  -type  lef  -tag  my_ex-
                tract_v1

                commit_module_model               -mmmc_file               de-
                sign/dtmf_recvr_core.enc.dat/viewDefinition.tcl

                earlyGlobalRoute

                write_module_model_context  -cell  ptn_wrapper   -tag   my_ex-
                tract_v1  -type_specific_options  {-extension  50 -ground vss1
                init} -type extraction_context

